.TH "insert" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
insert \- Insert record or records into the current collection.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]db.collectionspace.collection.insert(<doc|docs>,[flag])\f[]
.PP
\f[B]db.collectionspace.collection.insert(<doc|docs>,[options])\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
Collection
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Insert record or records into the current collection.
If the current collection does not exist, please create it first.
.PP
\f[B]Note：\f[]
.PP
When the provided record does not have an "_id" field, the database will add one
for it.
.SH PARAMETERS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]doc/docs\f[] ( \f[I]Object/Array of Object\f[]， \f[I]Required\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
Record or records to be inserted.
Can not be null.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]flag\f[] ( \f[I]Int32\f[]， \f[I]Optional\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
Insert flag, use to control the behavior of inserting.
Can be the follow value:
.IP \[bu] 2
0, default value.
.IP \[bu] 2
SDB_INSERT_RETURN_ID, means return the value of "_id" field of the record.
.IP \[bu] 2
SDB_INSERT_CONTONDUP, means continue inserting (no errors were reported) when
hitting index key duplicate error.
.IP \[bu] 2
SDB_INSERT_REPLACEONDUP, means replace the exist value to the inserting value
when hitting index key duplicate error, and continue the left records (no errors
were reported).
.RE
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.PP
when inserting a single record, the available flag
is：SDB_INSERT_RETURN_ID、SDB_INSERT_REPLACEONDUP
.PP
when inserting multiple records, the available flag
is：SDB_INSERT_CONTONDUP、SDB_INSERT_REPLACEONDUP
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]options\f[] ( \f[I]Object\f[]， \f[I]Optional\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
Options for control the behavior of inserting.
Can be the follow options:
.IP \[bu] 2
ContOnDup(Bool): represent whether insert continue(no errors were reported) when
hitting index key duplicate error.
.IP \[bu] 2
ReturnOID(Bool): represent whether insert return the "_id" field of the record
for user.
.IP \[bu] 2
ReplaceOnDup(Bool): represent whether replace the exist value to the inserting
value when hitting index key duplicate error, and continue the left records (no
errors were reported).
.PP
Format: { ContOnDup: true, ReturnOID: false }
.RE
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
On success, the follow result will be returned:
.IP \[bu] 2
When insert a single record with the flag of "SDB_INSERT_RETURN_ID", return the
value of "_id" field(Only when the value of "_id" field is type of ObjectId.
For the other element type, return a 12 bytes string which is
"000000000000000000000000" ).
.IP \[bu] 2
When using the "ReturnOID" options to control the insert behavior, a Json object
will be returned.
.IP \[bu] 2
Void for the other situations.
.PP
On error, exception will be thrown.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
the exceptions of \f[C]insert()\f[] are as below:
