.PP
when exception happen, use getLastError() to get the error code and use
getLastErrMsg() to get error message.
For more detial, please reference to Troubleshooting.
.SH HISTORY
.PP
Since v1.0.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP "1." 3
Insert a record.
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.bar.insert(\ {\ name:\ "Tom",\ age:\ 20\ }\ )
\f[]
.fi
.RE
.IP "2." 3
Insert some records.
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.bar.insert(\ [\ {\ _id:\ 20,\ name:\ "Mike",\ age:\ 15\ },\ {\ name:\ "John",\ age:\ 25,\ phone:\ 123\ }\ ]\ )
\f[]
.fi
.RE
.IP "3." 3
Insert records with duplicate index keys.
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.bar.insert(\ [\ {\ _id:\ 1,\ a:\ 1\ },\ {\ _id:\ 1,\ b:2\ },\ {\ _id:\ 3,\ c:\ 3\ }\ ],\ \ SDB_INSERT_CONTONDUP\ )
\f[]
.fi
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.bar.find()
{
\ \ \ \ "_id":\ 1,
\ \ \ \ "a":\ 1,
}
{
\ \ \ \ "_id":\ 3,
\ \ \ \ "c":\ 3
}
\f[]
.fi
.RE
.IP "4." 3
Insert record, and return Json object.
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.bar.insert({a:1},\ {ReturnOID:true,\ ContOnDup:true})
{
\ \ \ \ "_id":\ {
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ "$oid":\ "5becec3d6404b9295a63caca"
\ \ \ \ }
}
\f[]
.fi
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.bar.insert([{a:1},\ {b:1}],\ {ReturnOID:true,\ ContOnDup:true})
{
\ \ \ \ "_id":\ [
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ {
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ "$oid":\ "5bececdf6404b9295a63cacb"
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ },
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ {
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ "$oid":\ "5bececdf6404b9295a63cacc"
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ }
\ \ \ \ ]
}
\f[]
.fi
.RE
